tly the base_ron value.\n\nIf kagayaki (dealer) rons 浅梦 for mangan: dealer mangan = 12000. So 浅梦 loses 12000.\nBut expected says \"8000以上\" — that's less than dealer mangan.\n\nI think perhaps the danger zone is checking from the **victim's point perspective**: the victim loses X points, and we check for which X the promotion condition changes. The thresholds are then displayed as multiples of standard child ron values since those are the \"natural\" point units people think in.\n\nActually, maybe the expected output has a typo or I'm misunderstanding the format. Let me try running my calculator with just raw numbers and see if the overall logic produces results that are close to expected.\n\nLet me step back and try a different approach entirely. Instead of trying to match the expected output exactly with named labels, let me:\n1. Always display raw numbers (no 満貫/跳満/etc. labels)\n2. Use the correct attacker scores (DEALER_RON for dealer, CHILD_RON for child)\n3. See what comes out\n\nFor the special case where the \"3倍役满\" label appears, it seems to be used as a cap (the maximum). Let me just use raw numbers everywhere:",
